description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dartford and Gravesham NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post: Trust Grade (CT1/2 level) Doctor in General Medicine &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directorate: General Medicine &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract: Fixed-term for 1 year in the first instance, starting as soon as possible with the possibility of extension.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dartford and Gravesham NHS Trust is seeking to appoint 5 whole-time equivalent Trust Grade (CT1/2 level) Doctor in General Medicine to be based at the Darent Valley Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is available immediately for 1 year in the first instance, further extensions to be agreed mutually.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will join an established Team as a Trust Grade (CT1/2 level) Doctor providing outpatient and inpatient care for patients. This post will be part of an on-call rota, and will therefore attract a banding supplement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The potholder will be able to fully participate in the training programme directed by the Director of Medical Education, which will include formal teaching sessions, directed and self-directed personal learning, structured appraisals and assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have full GMC Registration with a licence to practice to be considered for this role and have completed foundation training or have equivalent experience. Computer literacy and a good standard of written and spoken English are both essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we offer a great opportunity to gain experience, in a location that&#39;s just 24 minutes by train from Central London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply for the position using the &quot;Apply for this job&quot; button. Please complete the online application form and include the full names, work addresses and fax numbers of three clinical referees, one of which must be your current or most recent employer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Shortlisting details and interview arrangements will be communicated via email therefore please ensure you check your email account regularly following the closing date. In addition the Trust will be chasing up references via email so please ensure you include the email addresses and contact numbers for your referees to avoid delay in the recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date is Sunday 22nd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Jonathan KwanJob titleDivisional Medical DirectorEmail addressjonathankwan@nhs.netTelephone number01322 428100&lt;/p&gt;
